1
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
[Episode 12:
You Had No Idea How Much I Loved You]

2
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
No wonder it looks so familiar.

3
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
It's our high school story.

4
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,832
Art comes from life.

5
00:01:18,832 --> 00:01:20,040
What did you write?

6
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:21,952
Can I be the female lead?

7
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:24,200
The revenge of a top student?

8
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,986
The temptation to return to the village?

9
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:32,811
Can't you cover it with this hand? Idiot!

10
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:51,080
A scriptwriter may write on many themes.

11
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:53,723
First, his own IP.

12
00:01:53,723 --> 00:01:55,439
Get to the point.

13
00:01:55,439 --> 00:01:57,680
The theme is not proposed by me,

14
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,319
but set by Party A.

15
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:02,432
First love is their preset theme.

16
00:02:03,025 --> 00:02:04,040
Oh.

17
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:07,120
I'm neither interested nor good at it.

18
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:09,520
So it's based on my own experience.

19
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:11,480
Having loved only once,

20
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:13,960
I had to write about it.

21
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,762
Not interested but accepted?

22
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,865
It pays well.

23
00:02:19,039 --> 00:02:21,080
When we were together,

24
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:25,400
you pursued art and good content.

25
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,909
You need money to be happy.

26
00:02:28,562 --> 00:02:30,255
That's what you taught me.

27
00:02:31,039 --> 00:02:33,147
Then you must be happy now.

28
00:02:36,232 --> 00:02:37,432
Yeah.

29
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,255
<i>What does he mean by "now"?</i>

30
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:46,480
<i>Anything to do with me?</i>

31
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:48,480
<i>No.</i>

32
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:50,755
<i>How should I reply?</i>

33
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:54,125
And here,

34
00:02:54,765 --> 00:02:56,560
"insomnia because of a senior".

35
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:58,342
It's not true!

36
00:02:59,599 --> 00:03:00,600
So it's because...

37
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,698
Because I was overjoyed that night.

38
00:03:02,698 --> 00:03:04,440
I spun around with my dress at home,

39
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:07,440
broke the alarm clock on the table,

40
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:09,146
and overslept the next morning.

41
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:11,960
Delete the part with him.

42
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:14,360
So it wasn't because of him?

43
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,010
It was because of you.

44
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:24,800
Yes.

45
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,518
You had no idea how much I loved you.

46
00:03:27,518 --> 00:03:30,120
I thought you had a crush on Jiang He.

47
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:32,225
So I imitated her.

48
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,491
Isn't it funny?

49
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,560
Why don't you continue?

50
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,106
I'm sleepy.

51
00:03:46,930 --> 00:03:48,640
I'm considering how to wrap up

52
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:50,400
the supporting male role.

53
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,235
It's easy.

54
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:56,869
He's so handsome!

55
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,468
He's so handsome!

56
00:04:00,159 --> 00:04:01,483
Hurry, hurry.

57
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:05,078
Senior, this is for you.

58
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:07,752
Thank you.

59
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,436
Let's go, let's go.

60
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,316
Go?

61
00:04:29,759 --> 00:04:31,640
Don't you want his QQ number?

62
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:32,879
Forget it.

63
00:04:32,879 --> 00:04:35,323
I didn't notice his big flaring nostrils

64
00:04:35,323 --> 00:04:36,926
until I got closer.

65
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,680
He spilled water everywhere

66
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,720
and wiped it with his sleeve.

67
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,682
So messy!

68
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,160
- That's it?
- That's it.

69
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,054
What then?

70
00:04:52,054 --> 00:04:53,537
Nothing.

71
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,730
In other words,

72
00:04:55,730 --> 00:04:59,199
if they meet again years later,

73
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:01,416
will they share a drink?

74
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:05,027
Guess.

75
00:05:06,255 --> 00:05:07,960
Since we've reached an agreement,

76
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:09,234
then

77
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:12,420
I wish us a pleasant collaboration.

78
00:05:12,420 --> 00:05:14,170
Wish us a pleasant collaboration.

79
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,507
Here.

80
00:05:57,992 --> 00:05:59,054
Let me do it.

81
00:05:59,054 --> 00:06:01,401
I don't want to keep troubling you.

82
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:07,082
The sun in Nanwan is harsh, right?

83
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,451
I wanted to get an even tan,

84
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,718
so I took off my ring.

85
00:06:20,577 --> 00:06:22,920
I noticed it when we met that day.

86
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,800
A nice wedding ring.

87
00:06:28,079 --> 00:06:29,560
I have something to do today.

88
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,041
So I'm not drinking for now.

89
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,399
- As for collaboration...
- As for collaboration,

90
00:06:33,399 --> 00:06:36,071
I appreciate your trust.

91
00:06:37,499 --> 00:06:40,205
I'll drink three toasts to you
to show my sincerity.

92
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:43,760
To our pleasant collaboration.

93
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,979
To our pleasant collaboration.

94
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,127
Scumbag.

95
00:07:33,879 --> 00:07:36,173
But the wine tastes good.

96
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:44,759
Sir, two more please.

97
00:07:44,759 --> 00:07:46,008
Okay.

98
00:07:53,079 --> 00:07:54,385
No idea.

99
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,226
Anyway,

100
00:07:57,839 --> 00:08:00,865
it's... impossible.

101
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:33,114
She left.

102
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:18,800
Not me, but my friend--

103
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,040
Wait.

104
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:22,600
You go first.

105
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,360
Give me a good review later.

106
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,962
Oh. Alright.

107
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,036
Wait!

108
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:44,120
Okay.

109
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:45,160
Tell me

110
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:47,216
what the problem is.

111
00:10:47,216 --> 00:10:48,400
My friend and her ex

112
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,480
held hands and spent a night alone.

113
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:53,608
She pretended to be asleep
to see his true reaction,

114
00:10:53,608 --> 00:10:55,718
but fell asleep as a result.

115
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,494
Nothing happened.

116
00:10:58,494 --> 00:10:59,833
Oh.

117
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,480
No feelings left.

118
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:05,080
But my friend said
when she gets drunk with other men,

119
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:07,000
her ex would pick her up specially

120
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,146
and get angry about it.

121
00:11:11,399 --> 00:11:13,877
Your friend's ex

122
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,781
is impotent.

123
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,822
Really?

124
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,559
Isn't it obvious?

125
00:11:20,559 --> 00:11:23,099
She'd certainly think he is...

126
00:11:25,279 --> 00:11:26,903
impotent.

127
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,759
No need to be so pessimistic.

128
00:11:29,759 --> 00:11:30,919
Generally speaking,

129
00:11:30,919 --> 00:11:33,720
men and women have different power.

130
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,000
If a man takes the initiative

131
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,759
when a woman is drunk,

132
00:11:36,759 --> 00:11:38,200
he's a rogue.

133
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,360
But if a woman takes the initiative,

134
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:42,360
then it's a different story.

135
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:45,519
So women have the initiative.

136
00:11:45,519 --> 00:11:47,720
It's reasonable for men to stay put.

137
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:49,399
Bro, you've dated a lot, haven't you?

138
00:11:49,399 --> 00:11:51,360
No, I'm always single.

139
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:54,159
I learn from this!

140
00:11:54,159 --> 00:11:56,545
What a coincidence. Me too.

141
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,480
After holding hands,

142
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:07,606
she said "continue", right?

143
00:12:08,559 --> 00:12:12,639
It sounds like "well, let it be".

144
00:12:12,639 --> 00:12:13,639
Quite reluctant.

145
00:12:13,639 --> 00:12:15,570
- Hopeless.
- Powerless.

146
00:12:15,570 --> 00:12:16,600
Helpless.

147
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,280
So it's reasonable that she left

148
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:19,840
without a farewell.

149
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:21,960
What a pity! What a pity!

150
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:24,188
I thought they could get together.

151
00:12:26,552 --> 00:12:28,200
Am I... wrong?

152
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:30,640
Our goal is not to get them together,

153
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,728
but to make her regret it.

154
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,857
How to...

155
00:12:39,486 --> 00:12:41,270
make her regret it?

156
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:55,046
[It's not a coincidence, I met you on purpose.]

157
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,240
Sorry, we...

158
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,960
It's me.

159
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,733
I come to cook.
